quran[9]{c,v,t}:
  12,87,"Go, my sons, and seek tidings of Joseph and his brother, and despair not of God's mercy, for none but the unbelieving despair of the mercy of God"
  12,88,"And when they came in to Joseph, they said, \"O Prince, distress hath reached us and our family, and little is the money that we have brought. But give us full measure, and bestow it as alms, for God will recompense the almsgivers"
  12,89,"He said, \"Know ye what ye did to Joseph and his brother in your ignorance"
  12,90,"They said, \"Canst thou indeed be Joseph?\" He said, \"I am Joseph, and this is my brother. Now hath God been gracious to us. For whoso feareth God and endureth. . . . God verily will not suffer the reward of the righteous to perish"
  12,91,"They said, \"By God! now hath God chosen thee above us, and we have indeed been sinners"
  12,92,"He said, \"No blame be on you this day. God will forgive you, for He is the most merciful of those who shew mercy"
  12,93,"Go ye with this my shirt and throw it on my father's face, and he shall recover his sight: and bring me all your family"
  12,94,"And when the caravan was departed, their father said, \"I surely perceive the smell of Joseph: think ye that I dote"
  12,95,"They said, \"By God, it is thy old mistake"